name: Knight
tID_INFO: A tough melee fighter. The Barbarian's handsome, cultured cousin. Rumor has it that he was knighted based on the sheer awesomeness of his mustache alone.

name: Archer
tID_INFO: A pair of lightly armored ranged attackers. They'll help you take down ground and air units, but you're on your own with hair coloring advice.

name: Goblins
tID_INFO: Three fast, unarmored melee attackers. Small, fast, green and mean!

name: Giant
tID_INFO: Slow but durable, only attacks buildings. A real one-man wrecking crew!

name: Pekka
tID_INFO: A heavily armored, slow melee fighter. Swings from the hip, but packs a huge punch.

name: Minions
tID_INFO: Three fast, unarmored flying attackers. Roses are red, minions are blue, they can fly, and will crush you!

name: Balloon
tID_INFO: As pretty as they are, you won't want a parade of THESE balloons showing up on the horizon. Drops powerful bombs and when shot down, crashes dealing area damage.

name: Witch
tID_INFO: Summons Skeletons, shoots destructo beams, has glowing pink eyes that unfortunately don't shoot lasers.

name: Barbarians
tID_INFO: A horde of melee attackers with mean mustaches and even meaner tempers.

name: Golem
tID_INFO: Slow but durable, only attacks buildings. When destroyed, explosively splits into two Golemites and deals area damage!

name: Skeletons
tID_INFO: Three fast, very weak melee fighters. Surround your enemies with this pile of bones!

name: Valkyrie
tID_INFO: Tough melee fighter, deals area damage around her. Swarm or horde, no problem! She can take them all out with a few spins.

name: SkeletonArmy
tID_INFO: Spawns an army of Skeletons. Meet Larry and his friends Harry, Gerry, Terry, Mary, etc.

name: Bomber
tID_INFO: Small, lightly protected skeleton that throws bombs. Deals area damage that can wipe out a swarm of enemies.

name: Musketeer
tID_INFO: Don't be fooled by her delicately coiffed hair, the Musketeer is a mean shot with her trusty boomstick.

name: BabyDragon
tID_INFO: Burps fireballs from the sky that deal area damage. Baby dragons hatch cute, hungry and ready for a barbeque.

name: Prince
tID_INFO: Don't let the little pony fool you. Once the Prince gets a running start, you WILL be trampled. Deals double damage once he gets charging.

name: Wizard
tID_INFO: The most awesome man to ever set foot in the Arena, the Wizard will blow you away with his handsomeness... and/or fireballs.

name: MiniPekka
tID_INFO: The Arena is a certified butterfly-free zone. No distractions for P.E.K.K.A, only destruction.

name: SpearGoblins
tID_INFO: Three unarmored ranged attackers. Who the heck taught these guys to throw spears!? Who thought that was a good idea?!

name: GiantSkeleton
tID_INFO: The bigger the skeleton, the bigger the bomb. Carries a bomb that blows up when the Giant Skeleton dies.

name: HogRider
tID_INFO: Fast melee troop that targets buildings and can jump over the river. He followed the echoing call of \qHog Riderrrrr\q all the way through the Arena doors.

name: MinionHorde
tID_INFO: Six fast, unarmored flying attackers. Three's a crowd, six is a horde!

name: IceWizard
tID_INFO: This chill caster throws ice shards that slow down enemies' movement and attack speed. Despite being freezing cold, he has a handlebar mustache that's too hot for TV.

name: RoyalGiant
tID_INFO: Destroying enemy buildings with his massive cannon is his job; making a raggedy blond beard look good is his passion.

name: SkeletonWarriors
tID_INFO: Three ruthless bone brothers with shields. Knock off their shields and all that's left are three ruthless bone brothers.

name: Princess
tID_INFO: This stunning Princess shoots flaming arrows from long range. If you're feeling warm feelings towards her, it's probably because you're on fire.

name: DarkPrince
tID_INFO: The Dark Prince deals area damage and lets his spiked club do the talking for him - because when he does talk, it sounds like he has a bucket on his head.

name: ThreeMusketeers
tID_INFO: Trio of powerful, independent markswomen, fighting for justice and honor. Disrespecting them would not be just a mistake, it would be a cardinal sin!

name: LavaHound
tID_INFO: The Lava Hound is a majestic flying beast that attacks buildings. The Lava Pups are less majestic angry babies that attack anything.

name: IceSpirits
tID_INFO: Spawns one lively little Ice Spirit to freeze a group of enemies. Stay frosty.

name: FireSpirits
tID_INFO: These three Fire Spirits are on a kamikaze mission to give you a warm hug. It'd be adorable if they weren't on fire.

name: Miner
tID_INFO: The Miner can burrow his way underground and appear anywhere in the Arena. It's not magic, it's a shovel.

name: ZapMachine
tID_INFO: Sparky slowly charges up, then unloads MASSIVE area damage. Overkill isn't in her vocabulary.

name: Bowler
tID_INFO: This big blue dude digs the simple things in life - Dark Elixir drinks and throwing rocks. His massive boulders roll through their target, hitting everything behind for a strike!

name: RageBarbarian
tID_INFO: He chops trees by day and hunts The Log by night. His bottle of Rage spills everywhere when he dies.

name: BattleRam
tID_INFO: Two Barbarians holding a big log charge at the nearest building, dealing significant damage if they connect; then they go to town with their swords!

name: InfernoDragon
tID_INFO: Shoots a focused beam of fire that increases in damage over time. Wears a helmet because flying can be dangerous.

name: IceGolemite
tID_INFO: He's tough, targets buildings and explodes when destroyed, slowing nearby enemies. Made entirely out of ice... or is he?! Yes.

name: MegaMinion
tID_INFO: Flying, armored and powerful. What could be its weakness?! Cupcakes.

name: BlowdartGoblin
tID_INFO: Runs fast, shoots far and chews gum. How does he blow darts with a mouthful of Double Trouble Gum? Years of didgeridoo lessons.

name: GoblinGang
tID_INFO: Spawns five Goblins - three with knives, two with spears - at a discounted Elixir cost. It's like a Goblin Value Pack!

name: ElectroWizard
tID_INFO: He lands with a \qPOW!\q, stuns nearby enemies and shoots lightning with both hands! What a show off.

name: AngryBarbarians
tID_INFO: Spawns a pair of leveled up Barbarians. They're like regular Barbarians, only harder, better, faster and stronger.

name: Hunter
tID_INFO: He deals BIG damage up close - not so much at range. What he lacks in accuracy, he makes up for with his impressively bushy eyebrows.

name: AxeMan
tID_INFO: He throws his axe like a boomerang, striking all enemies on the way out AND back. It's a miracle he doesn't lose an arm.

name: Assassin
tID_INFO: The Bandit dashes to her target and delivers an extra big hit! While dashing, she can't be touched. The mask keeps her identity safe, and gives her bonus cool points!

name: RoyalRecruits
tID_INFO: Deploys a line of recruits armed with spears, shields and wooden buckets. They dream of ponies and one day wearing metal buckets.

name: DarkWitch
tID_INFO: Summons Bats to do her bidding, even after death! If you get too close, she isn't afraid of pitching in with her mean-looking battle staff.

name: Bats
tID_INFO: Spawns a handful of tiny flying creatures. Think of them as sweet, purple... balls of DESTRUCTION!

name: Ghost
tID_INFO: He drifts invisibly through the Arena until he's startled by an enemy... then he attacks! Then he's invisible again! Zzzz.

name: REPLACEWR
tID_INFO: A tough melee fighter. The Barbarian's handsome, cultured cousin. Rumor has it that he was knighted based on the sheer awesomeness of his mustache alone.

name: MiniSparkys
tID_INFO: Spawns a pack of miniature Zap machines. Who controls them...? Only the Master Builder knows.

name: Rascals
tID_INFO: Spawns a mischievous trio of Rascals! The boy takes the lead, while the girls pelt enemies from behind... with slingshots full of Double Trouble Gum!

name: MovingCannon
tID_INFO: A Cannon on wheels?! Bet they won't see that coming! Once you break its shield, it becomes a Cannon not on wheels.

name: MegaKnight
tID_INFO: He lands with the force of 1,000 mustaches, then jumps from one foe to the next dealing huge area damage. Stand aside!

name: SkeletonBalloon
tID_INFO: It's a Skeleton party in the sky, until all the balloons pop... then it's a Skeleton party on the ground!

name: DartBarrell
tID_INFO: The Master Builder has sent his first contraption to the Arena! It's a fast and fun flying machine, but fragile!

name: NOTINUSEEG
tID_INFO: A tough melee fighter. The Barbarian's handsome, cultured cousin. Rumor has it that he was knighted based on the sheer awesomeness of his mustache alone.

name: RoyalHogs
tID_INFO: The King's personal pets are loose! They love to chomp on apples and towers alike - who let the hogs out?!

name: GoblinGiant
tID_INFO: This jolly green Goblin Giant stomps towards enemy buildings. He carries two Spear Goblins everywhere he goes. It's a weird but functional arrangement.

name: NOTINUSECH
tID_INFO: A tough melee fighter. The Barbarian's handsome, cultured cousin. Rumor has it that he was knighted based on the sheer awesomeness of his mustache alone.

name: EliteArcher
tID_INFO: Not quite a Wizard, nor an Archer - he shoots a magic arrow that passes through and damages all enemies in its path. It's not a trick, it's magic!

name: REPLACEED
tID_INFO: A tough melee fighter. The Barbarian's handsome, cultured cousin. Rumor has it that he was knighted based on the sheer awesomeness of his mustache alone.

name: NOTINUSEAM
tID_INFO: A tough melee fighter. The Barbarian's handsome, cultured cousin. Rumor has it that he was knighted based on the sheer awesomeness of his mustache alone.

name: REPLACEWB
tID_INFO: A tough melee fighter. The Barbarian's handsome, cultured cousin. Rumor has it that he was knighted based on the sheer awesomeness of his mustache alone.
